INSERT INTO `question`(`section`, `question_content`, `a`, `b`, `c`, `d`, `ans`, `sub_section`, `level`, `solution`, `date_posted`) VALUES ('Chemistry','Considering entropy (S) as a thermodynamic parameter, the criterion for thespontaneity of any process is','(a)\\(\\Delta {S_{system}} > 0\\) only','(b)\\(\\Delta {S_{surroundings}} > 0\\) only','(c)\\(\\Delta {S_{system}} + \\Delta {S_{surroundings}} > 0\\)','(d)\\(\\Delta {S_{system}} - \\Delta {S_{surroundings}} > 0\\)','3','Theromodynamics and Thermochemistry-Final','2','Answer =  (c)\\(\\Delta {S_{system}} + \\Delta {S_{surroundings}} > O\\)(for spontaneity)Because of \\(\\Delta S = R\\ln \\frac{{{V_2}}}{{{V_1}}}\\)Here the volume of gas increase from \\({V_1}\\) to \\({V_2}\\) at constanttemperature T.The total increase in entropy of the system and its surrounding during thespontaneous process of expansion considered above is, thus\\(R\\,\\ln \\,\\left({\\frac{{{V_2}}}{{{V_1}}}} \\right)\\) since \\({V_2} > {V_1}\\) it is obvious thatthe spontaneous (irreversible) isothermal expansion of a gas is accompanied by anincrease in the entropy of the system and its surrounding considered together.\\(\\Delta {S_{system}} + \\Delta {S_{surroundings}} > 0.\\)',CURRENT_TIMESTAMP);
